f Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert d'Anvers II was born in 1172, in Tetsworth, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, William D'Anvers I, was 37 and his mother, Emma de Chevauchesul, was 31. He married Muriel of Oxfordshire. They were the parents of at least 4 sons. He died in 1223, in his hometown, at the age of 51."},"et":{"1172–1223":"1172–1223","1174–Male":"1174–Surnud","1178–Male":"1178–Surnud","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1182–Male":"1182–Surnud","1165–1200":"1165–1200","1194–Male":"1194–Surnud","1197–1246":"1197–1246","1199–Male":"1199–Surnud","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1135–1197":"1135–1197","1142–Female":"1142–Surnud","about 1194":"umbes 1194","1165":"1165","1197":"1197","1142":"1142","1174":"1174","1172":"1172","1194":"1194","1182":"1182","1180":"1180","Abt 1197":"umbes 1197","1246":"1246","1223":"1223","Abt 1167":"umbes 1167","1135":"1135","1200":"1200","1178":"1178","1199":"1199","about 1200":"umbes 1200","about 1199":"umbes 1199","Tetsworth, Oxfordshire, England":"Tetsworth, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1172–1223":"1172–1223","1174–Male":"1174–Kuollut","1178–Male":"1178–Kuollut","1180–Male":"1180–Kuollut","1182–Male":"1182–Kuollut","1165–1200":"1165–1200","1194–Male":"1194–Kuollut","1197–1246":"1197–1246","1199–Male":"1199–Kuollut","1200–Male":"1200–Kuollut","1135–1197":"1135–1197","1142–Female":"1142–Kuollut","about 1194":"noin 1194","1165":"1165","1197":"1197","1142":"1142","1174":"1174","1172":"1172","1194":"1194","1182":"1182","1180":"1180","Abt 